 EXPERIMENTAL DATABASE                                            2634 1451
 --------------------                                             2634 1451
 The experimental database used in the evaluation is summarized   2634 1451
 in Table IX of the primary reference (NDS 148,241(2018)). In     2634 1451
 doing this selection we favored: (i) broad energy range covered  2634 1451
 by the experiment, (ii) high energy resolution, and (iii) high   2634 1451
 (but reasonable) accuracy of the experiment. Thus the            2634 1451
 measurements providing possibly wide and reliable picture were   2634 1451
 given precedence over single energy-point experiments,           2634 1451
 especially within the energy range where strong fluctuations     2634 1451
 were observed. On the other hand, many single- or a few-point    2634 1451
 measurements adopted when no extended datasets were              2634 1451
 available. Some of the measured datasets were renormalized to    2634 1451
 account for changes in the reference cross sections since they   2634 1451
 were used in the analysis of the experiments. The                2634 1451
 renormalizations built into the EXFOR retrieval system were      2634 1451
 adopted. In case of the (n,p) and (n,2n) reactions we took       2634 1451
 advantage of the existing high quality evaluations available     2634 1451
 from the IRDFF library (INDC(NDS)-0616, IAEA, Vienna (2012))     2634 1451
 and used these data instead of the actual measurements.          2634 1451
